\begin_layout Plain Layout
This is the idea of pecuniary emulation noted by Veblen
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "VeblenLeisureClass"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 i.e.
 the notion that the habits of the rich are emulated by the poorer consumers.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 , extreme wealth differences thus have the effect of making status consumption
 appear futile to the poor consumers.
 Seeking conditions under which the demand for status goods is reduced in
 spatially or economically separated reference groups 
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The terminology of goods vs commodities provided by Cramer 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "CramerIncomePrice1973"
literal "false"

\end_inset

